Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
uiAdd(25.10)                                                      uiAdd(25.10)

Name
       uiAdd  -  Adds  a  new interface element with the specified name of the
       specified type

Syntax
       uiAdd

       [-help]

       <name>

       [-before <name>]

       [-checked {true | false}]

       [-command <string>]

       [-disabled {true | false}]

       [-enablevar <string>]

       [-foreground <string>]

       [-icon <filename>]

       [-in <name>]

       [-label <string>]

       [-menuseparate {true | false}]

       [-movable {true | false}]

       [-newline {true | false}]

       [-shortcut <string>]

       [-tooltip <string>]

       -type {menu | toolbar | submenu | command | check | radio | separator |
       toolbutton}

       [-underline <integer>]

       [-value <string>]

       [-variable <string>]

       [-visiblevar <string>]

       Adds a new interface element with the specified name of  the  specified
       type.  Use this command to customize the Innovus graphical interface by
       adding menus, toolbars, status bar, and other  interface  elements,  as
       required.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each uiAdd parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man uiAdd

       <name> Specifies as a string the internal name of the interface element
              you want to add.

              Note:  Choose the internal name of the element carefully as this
              is what is used internally by the software to identify the  ele-
              ment for any further manipulation.

       -before <name>
              When  specified, adds the new element before the element identi-
              fied by <name>.

       -checked {true | false}
              Specifies whether or not the check box or radio button  you  are
              adding should be checked.

              Note:  You can use the -checked parameter only if you are adding
              elements of type check or radio.

              Default: false

       -command <string>
              Specifies the Tcl command to be executed when  the  element  you
              are adding is invoked.

              Note:  You can use the -command parameter only if you are adding
              elements of type command, check, radio or toolbutton.

       -disabled {true | false}
              Specifies the state of the interface element you are adding.

              Note: You can use the -disabled parameter only if you are adding
              elements of type menu, submenu, command, check, radio  or  tool-
              button.  The  parameter  is  NOT applicable for elements of type
              toolbar and separator.

              Default: false

       -enablevar <string>
              Represents the Tcl global variable for Enable status.

       -foreground <string>
              Specifies foreground color of the icon.

              Note: You can use the -foreground  parameter  only  if  you  are
              adding an element of type toolbutton.

       -icon <filename>
              When  adding  a toolbutton, specifies the file name of the tool-
              button icon. <filename> can be the full path of the icon file or
              an icon name supported by Innovus.

              The icon names used in Innovus can be queried  using  the  uiGet
              command.

              For  list  of supported image formats for the icon file, see the
              "Supported Image Formats" section of the  Customizing  the  User
              Interface chapter in the Innovus User Guide.

              Note:  The  -icon  parameter  is applicable only for elements of
              type toolbutton.

       -in <name>
              Specifies the name of the parent  element.  Use  this  parameter
              along  with  -before  to specify the location of the element you
              are adding. By default, -in adds the element to the end  of  the
              parent element. Use -before to add the element at a specific lo-
              cation within the parent element.

              Note: If -in is not specified, the new element is created but is
              not added to any location.

       -label <string>
              Specifies the label to be displayed on the new element.

              Note: This parameter is NOT applicable for elements of type sep-
              arator.

       -menuseparate {true | false}
              Specifies  whether  or  not a menu or submenu being added can be
              torn off or detached.

              Note: This parameter is applicable for elements of type menu and
              submenu.

              Default: true

       -movable {true | false}
              When adding a toolbar, specifies whether or not it will be  mov-
              able.

       -newline {true | false}
              When  adding  a  toolbar,  specifies  whether or not the toolbar
              should be added as a new row.

              Note: The -newline parameter is applicable only for elements  of
              type toolbar.

              Default: false

       -shortcut <string>
              Specifies  the shortcut key for a command, check box, radio but-
              ton, or toolbutton.

              Note: You can use the -shortcut parameter only if you are adding
              elements of type command, check, radio, ortoolbutton.

       -tooltip <string>
              Specifies the tooltip text for the toolbar or toolbutton you are
              adding.

              Note: The -tooltip parameter is applicable only for elements  of
              type toolbar and toolbutton.

       -type {menu | toolbar | submenu | command | check | radio | separator |
       toolbutton}
              Specifies  the  type  of  the interface element you want to add.
              Currently, elements of type main and   statusbar  are  not  sup-
              ported.

       -underline <integer>
              Specifies the integer index of the character to be underlined in
              the  element  label.  The  index begins with 0 and should have a
              value less than or equal to the length of the element label. For
              instance, if you want the second letter of the element label  to
              appear underlined, specify <integer>as 1.

              Note: The -underline parameter is NOT applicable for elements of
              type toolbar, separator, and toolbutton.

              Note: This parameter can be used only if the -label parameter is
              also specified.

       -value <stringValue>
              When  adding a radio button, specifies the value to be stored in
              the associated variable when the radio button is selected.

              Note: The -value parameter is applicable only  for  elements  of
              type radio.

       -variable <string>
              When  adding  a  check  box  or  radio button, specifies the Tcl
              global variable for the item.

       -visiblevar <string>
              Represents the Tcl global variable for Visible status

Examples
              * The following command will add a new, non-detachable menu  la-
                beled ExampleMenu in the main window:

                uiAdd  exmpMenu  -type  menu  -label ExampleMenu -menuseparate
                false -in main

              * The following command will add a new menu item  labeled  Exam-
                pleCommand in ExampleMenu:

                uiAdd  exmpCommand  -type  command  -label  ExampleCommand -in
                exmpMenu -command [list puts Example Command]

              *

                The following command adds a new,  unmovable  toolbar  to  the
                layout window:

                uiAdd newTB -type toolbar -in main.layout -movable false

